-- monthly_subscription_metrics.sql
WITH billing_events_deduplicated AS (
  -- Pick one billing event per subscription/month combination
  SELECT 
    subscription_id,
    event_month,
    amount,
    ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY subscription_id, event_month ORDER BY event_id) AS rn
  FROM billing_events
),
filtered_billing_events AS (
  SELECT 
    subscription_id,
    event_month,
    amount
  FROM billing_events_deduplicated
  WHERE rn = 1
),
subscriptions_with_plan_tier AS (
  -- Join subscriptions with plans, handling missing plan_ids
  SELECT 
    s.subscription_id,
    s.user_id,
    s.plan_id,
    s.started_at,
    s.ended_at,
    s.status,
    COALESCE(p.tier, 'unknown') AS tier
  FROM subscriptions s
  LEFT JOIN plans p ON s.plan_id = p.plan_id
),
subscriptions_with_company AS (
  -- Join with users and companies, handling nullable company_id
  SELECT 
    s.subscription_id,
    s.user_id,
    s.started_at,
    s.ended_at,
    s.status,
    s.tier,
    COALESCE(c.industry, 'unknown') AS industry
  FROM subscriptions_with_plan_tier s
  LEFT JOIN users u ON s.user_id = u.user_id
  LEFT JOIN companies c ON u.company_id = c.company_id
),
monthly_metrics AS (
  SELECT 
    be.event_month AS month,
    swc.tier,
    swc.industry,
    COUNT(DISTINCT swc.subscription_id) AS active_subscriptions,
    SUM(be.amount) AS total_mrr,
    COUNT(DISTINCT swc.user_id) AS unique_users
  FROM filtered_billing_events be
  JOIN subscriptions_with_company swc ON be.subscription_id = swc.subscription_id
  GROUP BY be.event_month, swc.tier, swc.industry
)
SELECT 
  month,
  tier,
  industry,
  active_subscriptions,
  total_mrr,
  unique_users
FROM monthly_metrics
ORDER BY month, tier, industry;
